📝Finalmente a los 24' st nuevamente Ramon Sosa ponía el 3 a 0 definitivo y goleaba a Barracas de local.

📝Muy Buen partido de Talleres, anuló totalmente a los dirigidos por Rodo De Paoli y a su vez fue muy efectivo.

La pratica della ginnastica in gravidanza è ormai un'abitudine diffusa e consolidata; questo perché consente di godere di numerosi benefici sia per la madre che per il bambino, senza però trascurare eventuali controindicazioni ed effetti collaterali.
La verità è che non esistono assolutismi e tutto dev'essere interpretato come "relativo" e gli enti preposti suggeriscono semplicemente una serie di linee guida. Ogni gestazione è a sé stante e per questo risulta piuttosto difficile consigliare atteggiamenti specifici che garantiscano la buona riuscita della gravidanza. Rimane essenziale intervenire preventivamente – quando possibile – ma anche "sapersi ascoltare" e usare il buon senso.

Torschützinnen: 1x Manja 1x Oltiona und 2x Mücke 

"Eine recht zerfahrene Partie. Nachdem sich dieses Aufeinandertreffen in den letzten Jahren zum Dauerbrenner entwickelt hat und wir die letzten Spiele deutlich gewinnen konnten, trafen wir am Sonntag auf ein anderes Cordi. Man merkte deutlich den Schwung, den sie aus dem Sieg gegen Pauli mitgenommen haben. Das Spiel wurde über Standards entschieden, das 1:0 von Cordi nach einer Ecke, das 2:0 durch einen Elfer. Wir schossen unsere Tore ebenfalls nach 3 Ecken und einem Elfer.
Nicht immer schön anzuschauen, da beiderseits wenig Spielfluss zustande kam, aber das Spiel lebte von der Spannung und dem Ergebnisverlauf. In Summe leicht verdient, da wir die etwas besseren Chancen hatten. Wir dürften uns aber auch nicht beschweren, wenn es andersrum ausgegangen wäre." - Christian Kroll

Students and instructors of Leash Free Living had some nice success at trials these past weekend! 

On the student side, Team Leyland (Golden Retriever) showed in Rally Novice A and earned her 3rd qualifying leg for their Rally Novice title!! Team Rylie (Wheaton Terrier) finished their Rally Novice title as well, then moved up to the Rally Advanced class and earned their first Advanced leg!

On the instructor side, Team Lancelot (Jacqui & her Standard Poodle) competed in Rally and Agility! In Rally, they earned two more triple Qs towards their RACH title with a 2nd, a 3rd and two 4ths (that means they competed and qualified in the Advanced, Excellent and Masters Rally classes). He also qualified in 2 out of 3 Agility runs with one 1st place!

Team Yoshi (Jayna & her Catahoula mix) did Rally and had two qualifying Advanced B runs with a 3rd place and a 4th place! Only one more leg to go for their Rally Advanced title! 

Team Lemon (Sam & her schnoodle) did Rally and earned two Triple Qs (#14 and #15) towards her RACH title, with a 4th, a 2nd and two 1sts. They also won Highest Combined Triple Score at the second trial!

Great job, everyone!!
